article.description: Tyler Nelson scored 20 points and Fairfield edged Rider 69-64 on Saturday.
article.headline: Nelson scores 20, Fairfield edges Rider 69-64
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- Tyler Nelson scored 20 points and Fairfield edged Rider 69-64 on Saturday. Nelson was 5 of 9 from the floor and made all nine of his free throw attempts for the Stags (8-7, 2/3 Metro Atlantic). Marcus Gilbert scored 14 points with 10 rebounds and Jerome Segura finished with 11. Kahlil Thomas paced Rider (4-12, 0-5 Metro Atlantic) with 18 points and 13 boards. Teddy Okereafor had 14 points, Xavier Lundy scored 12 and Jimmie Taylor added 11. A close game throughout, Gilbert hit a 3-pointer with 42 seconds left to put Fairfield up 65-62. Thomas tipped one in to cut it to one, but Nelson made a pair from the line, and Okereafor's 3-point attempt with three seconds left was no good. Rider outrebounded Fairfield 51-35 but turned it over 14 times and went just 4 of 19 from beyond the arc.
